# Verify build before finishing

After any code change in this project, run `pnpm build` before claiming the work is complete.

- `pnpm lint` alone is not enough — TypeScript and Next.js bundling errors only surface at build time.
- Fix all build errors before handing off; do not leave deploy-breaking issues for CI/production.
- If build fails, fix the root cause and re-run `pnpm build` until it passes.

Typical build-only failures to watch for:
- Client components importing server-only modules (e.g. `postgres`, `drizzle` DB code)
- Invalid type casts that pass ESLint but fail `tsc`
- Next.js App Router boundary violations
